<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The pointer parameter 'str' is modified inside MHD_str_has_token_caseless_. The function advances the pointer (e.g. while (' ' == *str || '\t' == *str || ',' == *str) str++; and const char sc = *(str++);), which alters the parameter value itself. Rule 17.8 forbids modifying pointer parameters (the pointed-to object may be modified, but not the pointer), so this is a violation.
</scenario>
